  "text": "In this case λ, µ necessarily lie in N N as well, that is, all the four λ ′ , µ ′ , λ, µ are partitions (with N parts). We have λ = (λ 1 , . . . , λ N ); we may and will assume that λ 1 > 0. We set n := |λ| + |µ|, and let D = k n . We fix a nilpotent endomorphism u of D, and a vector v ∈ D such that the type of GL(D)-orbit of the pair (u, v) is (λ, µ) (see [CITATION_1] , Theorem 1). By the definition of the structure constants in the spherical mirabolic bimodule, G u) . We consider the pair of partitions (ν, θ) = Υ(λ, µ) (notations introduced before Corollary 1 of [CITATION_2] ), so that ν = λ + µ is the Jordan type of u. We consider the dual partitionsν,θ. We consider the following flag of subspaces of Ker(u):",
